 the \\\"action\\\" should be advisory preparation when there’s guidance, though it’s not deterministic. Hmm, the key question is: Does the library need any setup beyond the normal test scaffold for meaningful coverage?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing configuration changes**\\n\\nI'm thinking the JUnit scaffold might already include what I need. However, it seems like there could be a config migration involved, especially since classic actors might require `pekko.actor.classic = on`. I should browse through the release notes to confirm this. This will help me avoid any errors and ensure everything is set up correctly for the project. Let's dive into those release notes to get the details!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DJAFb6ArqD4lt9ka2SrYDXqA|fc_0ce618590d6df5fd016a4060625d8c8196801e0be5c176efff", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nurl='https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/release-notes/releases-2.0.html'\nprint('URL',url)\ndata=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','ignore')\nfor needle in ['TypedActor', 'Removed', 'classic', 'Java serialization', 'pekko-actor-typed', '2.0.0-M1']:\n    print('\\nNEEDLE', needle)\n    idxs=[m.start() for m in re.finditer(re.escape(needle), data, re.I)]\n    print('count', len(idxs))\n    for i in idxs[:5]:\n        print(data[max(0,i-400):i+800].replace('\\n',' ')[:1300])\nPY", "timeout": 60}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mFHWzKF4zBcypB6gz1nH8jj1|fc_0ce618590d6df5fd016a4060625d9c819694a4b70d3e43cc17", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; for coord in 'org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor-typed_2.13:2.0.0-M1' 'org.apache.pekko:pekko-testkit_2.13:2.0.0-M1'; do IFS=: read g a v <<< \"$coord\"; url=\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/${g//.//}/$a/$v/$a-$v.jar\"; echo \"=== $coord ===\"; if curl -fsSLO \"$url\"; then jar tf \"$a-$v.jar\" | grep 'org/apache/pekko/actor/TypedActor\\|org/apache/pekko/actor/TypedProps\\|org/apache/pekko/actor/typed/ActorSystem' | head -30 || true; else echo missing; fi; done", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7023, "output": 1219, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28210, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782603859575, "responseId": "resp_0ce618590d6df5fd016a4060543118819698317b21a0ae291a"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_DJAFb6ArqD4lt9ka2SrYDXqA|fc_0ce618590d6df5fd016a4060625d8c8196801e0be5c176efff", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "URL https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/release-notes/releases-2.0.html\n\nNEEDLE TypedActor\ncount 0\n\nNEEDLE Removed\ncount 2\n> <p>This is milestone release and is aimed at testing this new major version by early adopters. This is experimental. This release should not be used in production.</p> <h3><a href=\"#main-changes\" name=\"main-changes\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Main changes</h3> <ul>   <li>Java 17 is the new minimum</li>   <li>Scala 2.12 support dropped</li>   <li>A lot of deprecated code removed</li>   <li>A lot of pekko.util classes for Scala version compatibility have been removed</li>   <li>Big change for all Java DSL users due to the removal of <code>pekko.japi.Function</code> (and related classes) to use <code>pekko.japi.function.Function</code> instead (lambdas should recompile ok but if you declared variables or functions explicitly, then you may need to change your imports)</li>   <li>New pekko-serialization-jackson3. Users who are happy with the pekko-serialization-jackson, which uses Jackson 2, can stick with that</li>   <li>Changed the pekko-serialization-jackson lz4-java dependency to <code>at.yawk.lz4:lz4-java</code>, a fork that has important bugfixes</li> </ul> <h3><a href=\"#upgrade-notes\" name=\"upgrade-notes\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span>\nopters. This is experimental. This release should not be used in production.</p> <h3><a href=\"#main-changes\" name=\"main-changes\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Main changes</h3> <ul>   <li>Java 17 is the new minimum</li>   <li>Scala 2.12 support dropped</li>   <li>A lot of deprecated code removed</li>   <li>A lot of pekko.util classes for Scala version compatibility have been removed</li>   <li>Big change for all Java DSL users due to the removal of <code>pekko.japi.Function</code> (and related classes) to use <code>pekko.japi.function.Function</code> instead (lambdas should recompile ok but if you declared variables or functions explicitly, then you may need to change your imports)</li>   <li>New pekko-serialization-jackson3. Users who are happy with the pekko-serialization-jackson, which uses Jackson 2, can stick with that</li>   <li>Changed the pekko-serialization-jackson lz4-java dependency to <code>at.yawk.lz4:lz4-java</code>, a fork that has important bugfixes</li> </ul> <h3><a href=\"#upgrade-notes\" name=\"upgrade-notes\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Upgrade notes</h3> <ul>   <li>Agrona was updated from 1.x to 2.x, which <a href=\"http\n\nNEEDLE classic\ncount 10\n<a href=\"../typed/dispatchers.html\" class=\"page\">Dispatchers</a></li>     <li><a href=\"../typed/mailboxes.html\" class=\"page\">Mailboxes</a></li>     <li><a href=\"../typed/testing.html\" class=\"page\">Testing</a></li>     <li><a href=\"../typed/coexisting.html\" class=\"page\">Coexistence</a></li>     <li><a href=\"../typed/style-guide.html\" class=\"page\">Style guide</a></li>     <li><a href=\"../typed/from-classic.html\" class=\"page\">Learning Pekko Typed from Classic</a></li>   </ul></li>   <li><a href=\"../typed/index-cluster.html\" class=\"page\">Cluster</a>   <ul>     <li><a href=\"../typed/cluster.html\" class=\"page\">Cluster Usage</a></li>     <li><a href=\"..